<L>__{interior rehearsal space day}
<A>__{delacroix sits in the first row with sloan, ruth, an african american casting director. levi, the musical director, also black, is on the stage at the piano.}
<B>__{audition montage}
<A>__{we see singers, magicians, dancers, acrobats, comedians, rappers. some good, most are terrible. many come out on stage dressed like mammies, stepin' fetchit, slaves, pimps, ho's, hustlers, and basketball players. it is a cavalcade of all the stereotypical roles one has seen.}
<B>__{angle on}
<A>__{space. lulu, a spoken word artist, goes her rendition of "way down on the swanee river."}
<C>__{delacroix }
<D>__{this was amazing. who had told these negroes that this was what we were looking for? the same old image, it damn for sure wasn't me.}
<B>__{close on}
<A>__{lulu.}
<D>__{delacroix (v.o.) (cont'd) were people this desperate to get work?}
<B>__{close on}
<A>__{delacroix. he interrupts lulu.}
